timeline.bodyText:
What's the idea here? If any batteryState is low, set the zoneList to OFF otherwise to ON?
homeHandler.getApi().listZones(homeId).forEach(zone -> {
    try {
        boolean batteryLow = !zone.getDevices().stream().map(ControlDevice::getBatteryState).anyMatch(s->!("NORMAL".equals(s)));
        zoneList.put(Long:valueOf(zone.getId()), OnOffType.from(batteryLow));
    } catch (IOException | ApiException e) {
        logger.debug("Fetch (battery state) zone list exception", e); 
    }
}

This also allows to process other zones if one zone failed (instead of before where processing stops when the first error occurs.

